diagnosis.differential_diagnosis: Acute myocardial ischemia, cardiac arrhythmia, hyperthyroidism, asthma, pheochromocytoma, opiate withdrawal, social anxiety disorder, generalized anxiety disorder, depression, substance abuse
diagnosis.diagnostic_reasoning: Ms. M has a lifelong history of anxiety and recent episodes of palpitations and chest discomfort associated with panic attacks. Normal results from blood tests and electrocardiograms, along with the clinical presentation of symptoms consistent with panic disorder, support this diagnosis. The patient was also able to control her symptoms using relaxation techniques and minimal medication.
